<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-542-002  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 542 002.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  June 4 1990 v36 n1812 p29(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Avionics marketing war seen shaping the decade. (Air ForceAdvanced Tactical Fighter, Army Light Helicopter; MilitaryElectronics supplement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Several important military upgrade contracts will determine thefuture of major players in the avionics industry during the 1990s.andO;The Air Force's Advanced Tactical Fighter (ATF), Army LightHelicopter (LH) and the F-16 Midlife Avionics Upgrade are amongthe contracts whose winners will hold strong market positionsuntil the year 2000.andP;  Few other programs will survive budget cuts,and some firms may be forced to phase out of the market.andP;  HughesAircraft is using a surface mount multichip package to fabricate achip-set computer for the ATF which will operate at 30 MIPS andcombine a common signal processor with a central mission computer.andO;Unisys provides the bus interface chip set in the Lockheed YF-23aircraft.andP;  A major bidding fight over the Boeing/Sikorskyprototype for the LH is likely, with HOneywell and Litton vyingfor RLG navigation contracts.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Defense ContractsAerospace IndustryUpgradingUnited States. Air ForceUnited States. NavyElectronic IndustryForecasting.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>